2. Pre-processing¶

Su tutti e 5 i dataset verrano eseguite le seguenti operazioni di pre-processing:

  • tokenizzazione
  • case folding
  • lemmatizzazione
  • rimozione delle stop words
  • rimozione di elementi superflui (emoji, segni di punteggiatura, spazi bianchi di troppo)

2.1 Lower case¶

2.2 Rimozione di emoji, punteggiatura e white spaces¶

In [14]:
# Emoji
def remove_emoji(text):
    emoji_pattern = re.compile("["
                               u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"  # emoticons
                               u"\U0001F300-\U0001F5FF"  # symbols & pictographs
                               u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"  # transport & map symbols
                               u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"  # flags (iOS)
                               u"\U00002500-\U00002BEF"  # chinese char
                               u"\U00002702-\U000027B0"
                               u"\U00002702-\U000027B0"
                               u"\U000024C2-\U0001F251"
                               u"\U0001f926-\U0001f937"
                               u"\U00010000-\U0010ffff"
                               u"\u2640-\u2642"
                               u"\u2600-\u2B55"
                               u"\u200d"
                               u"\u23cf"
                               u"\u23e9"
                               u"\u231a"
                               u"\ufe0f"  # dingbats
                               u"\u3030"
                               "]+", flags=re.UNICODE)
    return emoji_pattern.sub(r'', text)

# Punctuations
PUNCTUATIONS = string.punctuation
def remove_punctuation(text):
    trans = str.maketrans(dict.fromkeys(PUNCTUATIONS, ' '))
    return text.translate(trans)

def remove_whitespaces(text):
    return " ".join(text.split())

In [24]:
def lemmaSentence(token_words):
    lemma_text=[]
    for word in token_words:
        lemma_text.append(wordnet_lemmatizer.lemmatize(word))
    return lemma_text

2.5 Stop-words removal¶

In [27]:
nltk.download('stopwords')
STOPWORDS = set(stopwords.words('english'))
STOPWORDS =set(STOPWORDS)
#adding some of the stopwords after observing the tweets
STOPWORDS.add("the")
STOPWORDS.add("br")
STOPWORDS.add("i")
STOPWORDS.add("s")

STOPWORDS = list(STOPWORDS)

[nltk_data] Downloading package stopwords to /root/nltk_data...
[nltk_data]   Unzipping corpora/stopwords.zip.
In [28]:
def remove_stopwords(text):
  return [item for item in text if item not in STOPWORDS]

3. Word Cloud¶

Viene ora visualizzata una wordcloud per ogni dataset, cos da vedere se vengono visualizzate parole strane/prive di un significato apparente e da poter verificare se presente o no una coerenza tra i diversi commenti dei 5 dataset (a livello di lessico per lo meno).

In [ ]:
def conta (text):
    sentences= (list(itertools.chain(text)))
    flat_list = [item for sublist in sentences for item in sublist]
    c = Counter(flat_list)
    return c
In [ ]:
c_test_neg = conta(test_neg[0])
c_test_pos = conta(test_pos[0])
c_train_neg = conta(train_neg[0])
c_train_pos = conta(train_pos[0])
c_unsup = conta(unsup[0])
In [ ]:
def wordcloud (text):
    wc = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, max_words=50).generate_from_frequencies(text)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,10))
    plt.imshow(wc, interpolation="bilinear")
    plt.axis("off")
    return plt.show()
